remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-102">音声正規化は、特殊な構成体または書面での音声を表現するシンボルの使用です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-102">Speech normalization is the use of special constructs or symbols to express speech in writing.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-103">たとえば、認識されたテキストであるとします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-103">For example, suppose that this is recognized text:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-104">"12 30 1 午後 4 年 7 月に買った魚の 1 つのポイントの 6 つキログラム 14 ドル 6 セント、シアトルで市場を配置、姿勢でワシントン 9 8 1 つ 2 つ 2"</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-104">"july four at twelve thirty one PM, I bought one point six kilograms of fish for fourteen dollars and six cents, at the pike place market in seattle washington nine eight one two two"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-105">これは、正規化した後、同じテキストです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-105">This is the same text after normalization:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-106">「午後 12時 31分、7 月 4 日に買った魚の 1.6 kg $14.06, Seattle WA 98122 で市場を配置、姿勢で」</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-106">"July 4 at 12:31 PM, I bought 1.6 kg of fish for $14.06, at the pike place market in Seattle WA 98122"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-107">この例では、それぞれのインスタンスによって記述は 5 つの置換<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-107">In this example there are five substitutions, each of which would be described by an instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-108">使用して、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>オブジェクトをアプリケーションを判断できます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-108">Using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> object, an application can determine:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-109">場所と正規化で置換される語の数。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-109">The location and number of words replaced by normalization.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-110">詳細については、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A>」または」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-110">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A>.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-111">置換後のテキストとその属性を表示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-111">The replaced text and its display attributes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-112">詳細については、次を参照してください。 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>、および<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-112">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>, and  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-113">インスタンス<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>がのメンバーとして通常取得される、<xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601>によって返されるオブジェクト、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A>プロパティ<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>(から継承するクラスまたは<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>など<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>) 返されるテキストがされている場合正規化されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-113">Instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> are typically obtained as members of the <xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601> object returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A> property on <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> (or classes that inherit from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>, such as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>) when returned text has been normalized.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4fd1-114">次の例では、に関するユーザー インターフェイスで情報を表示、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>認識エンジンによって返されるオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4fd1-114">The example below displays information in a user interface about a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> object returned by a recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
internal static void DisplayBasicPhraseInfo(  
        Label label,   
        RecognizedPhrase result,   
        SpeechRecognizer rec)   
{  
  if (result != null && label != null)   
  {  
    // Blank  
    if (rec != null)   
    {   
      // Clear  
      label.Text += String.Format(  
                             "  Recognizer currently at:   {0} mSec\n" +  
                             "  Audio Device currently at: {1} mSec\n",  
                             rec.RecognizerAudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                             rec.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds);  
    }  
  
    if (result != null)   
    { // Clear  
      RecognitionResult recResult = result as RecognitionResult;  
      if (recResult != null)   
      {  
        RecognizedAudio resultAudio = recResult.Audio;  
        if (resultAudio == null)   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format("  Emulated input\n");  
        }   
        else   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                               "  Candidate Phrase at:       {0} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Phrase Length:             {1} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Input State Time:          {2}\n" +  
                               "  Input Format:              {3}\n",  
                               resultAudio.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.Duration.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.StartTime.ToShortTimeString(),  
                               resultAudio.Format.EncodingFormat.ToString());  
        }  
      }  
  
      label.Text += String.Format("  Confidence Level:          {0}\n", result.Confidence);  
      if (result.Grammar != null)   
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format(  
                            "  Recognizing Grammar:       {0}\n" +  
                            "  Recognizing Rule:          {1}\n",  
                            ((result.Grammar.Name != null) ? (result.Grammar.Name) : "None"),  
                            ((result.Grammar.RuleName != null) ? (result.Grammar.RuleName) : "None"));  
      }  
  
      if  (result.ReplacementWordUnits.Count !=  0)    
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format("  Replacement text:\n");  
        foreach (ReplacementText rep in result.ReplacementWordUnits)    
        {  
          string repText = rep.Text;  
          // Add trailing spaces  
  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.OneTrailingSpace) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += " ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.TwoTrailingSpaces) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += "  ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ConsumeLeadingSpaces) != 0)    
          {  
            repText=repText.TrimStart();  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ZeroTrailingSpaces) != 0)   
          {  
            repText = repText.TrimEnd();  
          }  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                           "      At index {0} for {1} words. Text: \"{2}\"\n",  
                           rep.FirstWordIndex,  rep.CountOfWords, repText);  
  
        }  
        label.Text += String.Format("\n\n");  
      }  
    }  
  }    
}  
```

  
  
